Title : Ahta River
Text : The '''Ahta River''' is a [[river]] in the [[British Columbia Coast|Central Coast of British Columbia]], flowing into [[Bond Sound]] to the south via the short '''Ahta Valley''',<ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/22614.html BC Names/GeoBC entry "Ahta Valley"]</ref> which connects to the head of [[Kingcome Inlet]] to the north.<ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/22615.html BC Names/GeoBC entry "Ahta River"]</ref>

[[Ahta Indian Reserve No. 3]], which is the site of a former Kwakwaka'wakw village named Hata or Hada or Ahta, is located at the mouth of the Ahta River.<ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/54850.html BC Names "Hata (Former First Nations village)"]</ref><ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/65363.html BC Names/GeoBC entry "Ahta 3 (Indian reserve)"]</ref>

